.TH "imr_remove_range" 9 "imr_remove_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
imr_remove_range \- delete an Isolated Memory Region by address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" imr_remove_range
.BI "(phys_addr_t base "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "base" 12
physical base address of region aligned to 1 KiB.
.IP "size" 12
physical size of region in bytes aligned to 1 KiB.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

This function allows you to delete an IMR by an address range specified
by base and size respectively.
imr_remove_range(base, size); delete IMR from base to base+size.
.SH "RETURN"
-EINVAL on invalid range or out or range id
-ENODEV if reg is valid but no IMR exists or is locked
0 on success.
